results.name: Denominators of the higher order exponential integral constants alpha(2,n).
comment: See A163927 for information about the constants alpha(k,n).
formula: alpha(k,n) = (1/k)*Sum_{i=0..k-1} Sum_{p=0..n-1} p^(-2*(k-i))*alpha(i, n) with alpha(0,n) = 1. For this sequence, k = 2 and n >= 1.
results.author: _Johannes W. Meijer_ & _Nico Baken_, Aug 13 2009, Aug 17 2009
